item.title: Threekly 1: The first Threekly!
item.description:
And thus begins my first weekly. A major point of this is exercise is to keep engaged and up to date with both current events and current media. I often find myself wishing I had kept more up-to-date with certain happenings, and this is my chance to mitigate any of that in the future. With that being said, let’s dive in to this week’s Threekly:

1. A thought problem I’ve been consumed with: Link to heading

Russell’s Paradox Link to heading

This video does a great job explaining it, but in short, it deals with Set Theory. Imagine a set that contains all sets that do not contain itself. Does this set contain itself? The rules of the set says it both should, and should not…
